    "comment": "Rationale: With respect to subcellular localization, immunohistochemical, biochemical, and electron microscopy analysis in rat brain clearly delineated that Sipa1l3/SPAR3 protein is present within the postsynaptic compartment (Fig. 3 and p. 34).\n\nSipa1l3/SPAR3 is found in synapses characterized by the presence of PSD95, VGLUT1 (Fig. 3b) and Bassoon (Fig. 4b) and is absent from synapses carrying GABAA receptors and VGAT (Fig. 3b).\n\nSipa1l3/SPAR3 bind to ProSAPiP1/Lzts3 - a component of the postsynaptic Shank scaffolding platform (Fig. 4d,e).. Experimental description: \"Rats from both sexes (Sprague-Dawley) were purchased from Charles River, Germany.\" (Materials and Methods/Animals and ethics statement, p. 29).\n\n\"Primary antibodies\nAn anti-Sipa1l3/SPAR3 antibody directed against the C-terminus of the protein (aa 1300-1776) was generated in rabbit after injection of a GST-SPAR3C-term fusion protein (anti-SPAR3, Pineda, Germany)\"",
